<template><div><h1 id="larvitar-installation-guide" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#larvitar-installation-guide"><span>Larvitar Installation Guide</span></a></h1>
<p>This guide walks you through the steps to install Larvitar and get it up and running. Larvitar is an open-source TypeScript library built on CornerstoneJS, designed for easy and efficient medical imaging applications.</p>
<h2 id="prerequisites" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#prerequisites"><span>Prerequisites</span></a></h2>
<p>Before installing Larvitar, make sure you have the following:</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Node.js</strong> (version 14.x or higher recommended)</li>
<li><strong>npm</strong> or <strong>yarn</strong> for package management</li>
</ul>
<p>You can check if Node.js and npm are installed by running:</p>
<div class="language-bash line-numbers-mode" data-highlighter="prismjs" data-ext="sh" data-title="sh"><pre v-pre><code><span class="line"><span class="token function">node</span> <span class="token parameter variable">-v</span></span>
<span class="line"><span class="token function">npm</span> <span class="token parameter variable">-v</span></span>
<span class="line"></span></code></pre>
<div class="line-numbers" aria-hidden="true" style="counter-reset:line-number 0"><div class="line-number"></div><div class="line-number"></div></div></div><h2 id="install-larvitar" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#install-larvitar"><span>Install Larvitar</span></a></h2>
<p>Add Larvitar to your project by running:</p>
<div class="language-bash line-numbers-mode" data-highlighter="prismjs" data-ext="sh" data-title="sh"><pre v-pre><code><span class="line"><span class="token function">npm</span> <span class="token function">install</span> larvitar</span>
<span class="line"></span></code></pre>
<div class="line-numbers" aria-hidden="true" style="counter-reset:line-number 0"><div class="line-number"></div></div></div><p>Alternatively, if you prefer yarn, use:</p>
<div class="language-bash line-numbers-mode" data-highlighter="prismjs" data-ext="sh" data-title="sh"><pre v-pre><code><span class="line"><span class="token function">yarn</span> <span class="token function">add</span> larvitar</span>
<span class="line"></span></code></pre>
<div class="line-numbers" aria-hidden="true" style="counter-reset:line-number 0"><div class="line-number"></div></div></div><h2 id="troubleshooting" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#troubleshooting"><span>Troubleshooting</span></a></h2>
<p>If you encounter any issues, try the following:</p>
<ul>
<li>Verify Dependencies: Make sure all peer dependencies like cornerstone-core and cornerstone-tools are correctly installed.</li>
<li>Node Compatibility: Larvitar works best with Node.js 14.x or higher.</li>
</ul>
<p>Still having trouble? Check out the <a href="https://github.com/dvisionlab/Larvitar/issues" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Issues section</a> on our GitHub page or contact our support.</p>
</div></template>


